PRETORIA - Some good news for Tshwane residents after it was initially estimated they would be without running water for up to eight months. Flood damage to a pump station left residents of Cullinan, Rayton, Refilwe, the Petra diamond mine and Zonderwater prison without water. READ: Tshwane residents urged to save water Acting mayor Abel Tau said there is an interim plan to get running water back to residents in a matter of weeks. Tau said the pipeline supplying the water and supporting structures of about 210m were washed away during recent floods. READ: Tshwane under pressure to get clean water to Hammanskraal He explained a temporary pump station would be erected on the other side of the dam and mounted to the water purification plant. The plant was not damaged during the inclement weather.